The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | ICC meeting
                                                                                                                       7                                      ICC meeting
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Efficacy of the Decision Review System (DRS) and the Future Tours Programme, including the venue for 2013 Champions Trophy will be on the agenda when the ICC Chief Executives Committee (CEC) meets here on Tuesday.         
	The CEC will receive an update on the successful implementation of the DRS in 13 Test matches in the last four months when the body convenes in Dubai on Tuesday for the first of its four meetings in 2010, an ICC release said.         
	On Wednesday and Thursday, the CEC will be joined by the representatives of the major cricket broadcasters, key staff within the full members and representatives of technology companies in a workshop.         
	During the meeting, CEC will also consider the location, duration and scheduling of ICC events for the period post-2012 and in particular the location of the ICC Champions Trophy in 2013.                                                                                                                     
